# Permission-first RBAC (locked)

## Non-negotiables

- **Authorization is permission-first.** Do not reintroduce **ADMIN** (or other role) as an unconditional bypass beside **`SUPER_ADMIN`** at the tRPC `permissionProcedure` layer.
- **Effective permissions** for non–SuperAdmin users = **role template ∪ legacy `role_permissions` ∪ `user_permissions` grants − revokes** (`PermissionsService.getEffectivePermissions`).
- **SUPER_ADMIN** is the only role that may be treated as full-catalog / immutable template semantics; keep **system templates `locked`** except documented emergencies.

